Upload a CSV File to Create a Dataset

Requirements:

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

Permissions Needed: Upload External Data to CRM Analytics

Uploading a CSV file:
Review the format requirements.
Ensure column names don't conflict with generated date column names.
Upload the file through the CRM Analytics Studio home tab or app page.
Select the file and click Next.
Enter a name for the dataset.
Choose an app where the dataset will be created.
Edit file properties if necessary.
Click Upload File.

Options while creating the dataset:
Cancel the process and stop dataset creation.
Close the progress dialog and leave the process running in the background.
Continue monitoring progress on the Monitor tab of Data Manager.
Do nothing, and explore the data when the dataset is created.

Also available: Use the External Data API to programmatically upload .csv files.
title: Uploading CSV Files in CRM Analytics
